        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 27 at 8:41PM MDT until July 27 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 840 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 19 miles northwest of Lothair to near Inverness,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Chester, Joplin, Inverness, and Whitlash.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.</instruction>
